                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.352,
                                "byte_start": 88575,
                                "byte_stop": 118041,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has the opinion in No. 04-593, Domino\u2019s Pizza versus McDonald."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.352,
                        "stop": 281.002,
                        "byte_start": 118041,
                        "byte_stop": 1212572,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.352,
                                "stop": 12.955,
                                "byte_start": 118041,
                                "byte_stop": 140402,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the 9th Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.955,
                                "stop": 22.804,
                                "byte_start": 140402,
                                "byte_stop": 179795,
                                "text": "The respondent, John McDonald, a black man, is the sole shareholder and president of JWM Investments, Inc."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.804,
                                "stop": 38.304,
                                "byte_start": 179795,
                                "byte_stop": 241862,
                                "text": "The petitioners here -- collectively, I will refer to them as \u201cDomino\u2019s Pizza\u201d -- contracted with McDonald\u0027s corporation, JWM, to construct four restaurants in the Las Vegas area."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.304,
                                "stop": 44.875,
                                "byte_start": 241862,
                                "byte_stop": 268088,
                                "text": "Problems developed between JWM and Domino\u2019s after the first restaurant was completed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.875,
                                "stop": 57.596,
                                "byte_start": 268088,
                                "byte_stop": 318975,
                                "text": "To make a long story short, the contracts between JWM and Domino\u2019s remained uncompleted, and at least in part for that reason JWM filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.596,
                                "stop": 71.988,
                                "byte_start": 318975,
                                "byte_stop": 376549,
                                "text": "In the bankruptcy proceedings, the breach-of-contract claim against Domino\u2019s was settled by the trustee in bankruptcy for $45,000, and JWM gave Domino\u2019s a complete release."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.988,
                                "stop": 84.443,
                                "byte_start": 376549,
                                "byte_stop": 426391,
                                "text": "In his personal capacity and separate from JWM\u2019s bankruptcy proceedings, McDonald\u0027s brought the present claim under 42 U.S.C. \u00a71981."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.443,
                                "stop": 100.958,
                                "byte_start": 426391,
                                "byte_stop": 492428,
                                "text": "This provision originally, part of the Civil Rights Act of 1866, protects the equal right of, \u201call persons within the jurisdiction of the United States to make and enforce contracts,\u201d without regard to race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.958,
                                "stop": 119.579,
                                "byte_start": 492428,
                                "byte_stop": 566929,
                                "text": "The statute defines the term \u201cmake and enforce contracts\u201d to, \u201cinclude the making, performance, modification and termination of contracts, and the enjoyment of all benefits, privileges, terms and conditions of the contractual relationship\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.579,
                                "stop": 131.301,
                                "byte_start": 566929,
                                "byte_stop": 613845,
                                "text": "McDonald alleged that Domino\u2019s broke its contract with JWM because of racial animas towards McDonald and that this breach harmed McDonald personally."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.301,
                                "stop": 141.65,
                                "byte_start": 613845,
                                "byte_stop": 655223,
                                "text": "The District Court granted Domino\u2019s motion to dismiss for failure to state a claim, since McDonald himself was party to no contract with Domino\u2019s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.65,
                                "stop": 144.881,
                                "byte_start": 655223,
                                "byte_stop": 668180,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the 9th Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.881,
                                "stop": 156.057,
                                "byte_start": 668180,
                                "byte_stop": 712902,
                                "text": "Relying on its own precedent, it concluded that McDonald\u0027s injury was, \u201cdistinct from that of the corporation,\u201d and that he therefore could bring his own 1981 claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.057,
                                "stop": 161.379,
                                "byte_start": 712902,
                                "byte_stop": 734113,
                                "text": "The 9th Circuit acknowledged that its approach set it apart from other circuits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.379,
                                "stop": 166.015,
                                "byte_start": 734113,
                                "byte_stop": 752712,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk, we reverse the judgment of the 9th Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.015,
                                "stop": 175.38,
                                "byte_start": 752712,
                                "byte_stop": 790119,
                                "text": "The contractual relationship that was allegedly impaired for racially discriminatory reasons was between Domino\u2019s and JWM."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.38,
                                "stop": 187.524,
                                "byte_start": 790119,
                                "byte_stop": 838707,
                                "text": "McDonald points out that in his capacity as president of JWM, he did, \u201cmake and enforce\u201d contracts for JWM."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.524,
                                "stop": 193.237,
                                "byte_start": 838707,
                                "byte_stop": 861591,
                                "text": "But the rights under those contracts belonged to JWM itself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.237,
                                "stop": 198.528,
                                "byte_start": 861591,
                                "byte_stop": 882697,
                                "text": "McDonald chose to conduct business through the corporate form and acted as agent of the corporation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.528,
                                "stop": 206.208,
                                "byte_start": 882697,
                                "byte_stop": 913417,
                                "text": "This carries with it certain advantages; for example, McDonald was not personally liable in JWM\u2019s bankruptcy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.208,
                                "stop": 208.877,
                                "byte_start": 913417,
                                "byte_stop": 924180,
                                "text": "But the bitter must be taken with the sweet."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.877,
                                "stop": 215.308,
                                "byte_start": 924180,
                                "byte_stop": 949884,
                                "text": "Here, the corporate form prevents McDonald from claiming JWM\u2019s injuries or rights as his own."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.308,
                                "stop": 234.85,
                                "byte_start": 949884,
                                "byte_stop": 1028043,
                                "text": "McDonald\u0027s role as an agent of JWM does not give him the ability to state a claim under 1981, because that statute does not protect one\u2019s right to act as the agent of someone else\u2019s contracting; it instead protects the right to give and receive contractual rights of one\u2019s own."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 234.85,
                                "stop": 245.392,
                                "byte_start": 1028043,
                                "byte_stop": 1070152,
                                "text": "McDonald alleges that his race was the reason Domino\u2019s breached its contracts with JWM and that he was the actual target of Domino\u2019s actions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.392,
                                "stop": 253.655,
                                "byte_start": 1070152,
                                "byte_stop": 1103275,
                                "text": "But the reason for the impairment does not change the fact that McDonald had no rights under the contractual relationship that was impaired."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.655,
                                "stop": 268.712,
                                "byte_start": 1103275,
                                "byte_stop": 1163462,
                                "text": "Section 1981 is a powerful remedy for racial discrimination in contracting, but it has always been limited to remedying race-based impairments to one\u2019s own existing or proposed contractual relationships."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 268.712,
                                "stop": 274.538,
                                "byte_start": 1163462,
                                "byte_stop": 1186763,
                                "text": "The 9th Circuit therefore erred in reversing the District Court\u2019s dismissal, and its judgment is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 274.538,
                                "stop": 281.002,
                                "byte_start": 1186763,
                                "byte_stop": 1212572,
                                "text": "The opinion is unanimous; Justice Alito took no part in the consideration or decision in the case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
